    "description": {
      "en": {
        "provenance": "imported",
        "value": "1. Selecting sites for the production of seeds out of season using various altitudes;2. Participatory identification and selection of local varieties and ecotypes of specific vegetable species;3. Scientific analysis of local varieties selected;4. Establishing groups of farmers and cooperatives along production chains;5. Improved production of fresh vegetables and selected spices in the production areas6. Promoting retailers and agricultural input suppliers7. Training the groups/cooperatives in the production of vegetables/seeds and produce out of season for processing and sale;8. Developing a system for handling, selecting and packaging the seeds;9. Construction and outfitting of infrastructure for the storage of non-perishable items, and identification/development of facilities designated as local collection centers;10. Training, roundtables with entrepreneurs and retailers, and the establishment of PGS protocols for technical support and product launch on the market11. Creation of an interactive network between cooperatives and producers to maximize national/regional/district market potential;12. Promoting bio-insecticides, bio-pesticides and bio-fertilizers13. Improving animal management and nutrition techniques (reduction in greenhouse gases) which are compatible with agricultural practices that can adapt to climate change."
      },
      "ne": null
    },
